      "chunk_index": 1,
      "summary": "Here’s a concise, step-by-step synthesis for making pizza at home:\n\n1. Prepare the dough\n\nMix 500 g bread flour (or Tipo 00/all-purpose), 2–2.5 tsp yeast, 1–2 tsp salt.\n\nAdd 300–338 ml lukewarm water and 1 tbsp olive oil; stir until shaggy.\n\nKnead 8–10 min until smooth and elastic.\n\nLet rise in a lightly oiled bowl, covered, 1–2 h at room temperature until doubled.\n\nPunch down, divide into balls, rest 15–20 min before shaping.\n\n2. Make the sauce\n\nCombine 1 can (≈400 g) crushed tomatoes, 1–3 minced garlic cloves, 1 tsp dried oregano, ½ tsp salt, pinch of sugar; optionally add olive oil, balsamic, or fresh basil.\n\nMix well; no cooking required for a fresh-tasting sauce.\n\n3. Assemble & bake\n\nPreheat oven as hot as possible (≈475–500 °F / 245–260 °C); use a pizza stone or heavy tray if available.\n\nStretch dough into rounds by hand, spread a thin layer of sauce, add desired toppings.\n\nBake 10–15 min until crust is golden and toppings are cooked.\n\nOptional: Refrigerate dough 24–48 h for deeper flavor and crisper crust.\n\nThis blends a practical home approach with flexibility for flavor and texture."
